      },
      "date": "2012-08-12 18:43:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nInstead of having inline #ifdef code, and to make it easier to submit code upstream with minimal changes, please define a macro like:\n\n #ifdef HAVE_VOID_MAKE_REQUEST_FN\n #define ll_mrf_ret void\n #define LL_MRF_RETURN(rc) EXIT\n #else\n #define ll_mrf_ret int\n #define LL_MRF_RETURN(rc) RETURN(rc)\n #endif\n\nThese can be used online in the code, and can easily be replaced with sed for upstream submission. \n\nFor GOTO, the typical usage is of the form:\n\n                GOTO(label, rc = PTR_ERR(ptr));",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
